Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.67,0:28:36.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}法拉弟已经知道通电后的电线具有磁性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Faraday knew that electric current turns a wire into a magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.96,0:28:39.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 他希望在电线外的铁屑中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so he expected to find related patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.33,0:28:42.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也能发现类似的图案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in iron filings around a wire carrying electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.68,0:28:46.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当其它人看到的只是好玩的图案时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where others saw merely lovely shapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.97,0:28:50.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}法拉弟则看得更为深远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Faraday saw something profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.67,0:28:55.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些图案不仅是铁屑的变化那么简单\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The patterns were not simply a quirk of iron filings;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.15,0:28:58.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们在磁铁的四周存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they existed in the space around a magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.15,0:28:59.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也在电流四周出现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or an electric current,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.72,0:29:02.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不管有没有铁屑出现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even in the absence of iron filings.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.29,0:29:04.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些图案就是轨迹 足迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The patterns were the traces, the footprints
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.02,0:29:07.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来自那看不见的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of invisible fields of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.16,0:29:11.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在任何一个磁性物体外都同样存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that reached out into the space around anything magnetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.30,0:29:18.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}指南针的原理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The compass needle that people wondered at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.27,0:29:20.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}曾让人类困扰了千年之久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a thousand years was not reacting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.01,0:29:23.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实并不是因为遥远的北极那里有块磁铁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to some far away magnetic North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.64,0:29:26.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而是因为连续不断的磁力场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was detecting a continuous force field
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.18,0:29:28.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无处不在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that stretched all the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.12,0:29:34.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球本身就是一块巨大的磁铁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth itself is a giant magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.59,0:29:36.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与其它磁铁类似\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And like any other magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.12,0:29:38.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的磁力线延展到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its lines of force extend far out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.62,0:29:41.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球四周的空间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the space surrounding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.13,0:29:44.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它围绕着我们 无处不在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're everywhere, all around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.26,0:29:46.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们一直存在着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've always been.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.03,0:29:48.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但从没有人注意过它们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But nobody had ever noticed them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.80,0:29:51.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者说 没有人类注意过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nobody human, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.97,0:29:57.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鸟类是恐龙的后裔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Birds are the last living descendants of the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.34,0:30:02.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鸽子与其它的鸟类同样具有出色的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pigeons and other birds are remarkably good
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.51,0:30:04.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}识别路途的能力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at finding their way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.45,0:30:07.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们能迁徙千里而不迷路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can migrate thousands of miles without getting lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:11.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们是怎么做到的 部分是由于可识别的地标\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How? Partly by recognizing familiar landmarks--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.89,0:30:14.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}例如河流 山脉 星辰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rivers, mountains, stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.29,0:30:15.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至是某种气味\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even certain smells can serve
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.99,0:30:19.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都能成为迁徙鸟类的路标\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as signposts for migrating birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.16,0:30:21.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鸟类的体内还有天然的罗盘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But birds also have an inner compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.73,0:30:24.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们能感应到地球的磁场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can actually sense the Earth's magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.97,0:30:28.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的大脑处理磁场数据的方式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their brains process magnetic data in much the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.74,0:30:31.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和人类处理视觉的方式很相似\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ours process visual data.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.34,0:30:33.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}依靠感应磁场方位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By sensing the direction of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.71,0:30:35.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鸟类能分辨南北\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}birds can tell north from south.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.81,0:30:38.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是为何北美洲的鸟类能够\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's one way North American birds know which way to go
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.85,0:30:40.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在冬天找到去往南方的路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they head south for the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.58,0:30:42.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球磁场在两极\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The field is stronger near the poles
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.92,0:30:44.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比赤道的要强\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than it is at the equator,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.76,0:30:48.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鸟类据此可以推断出它们所在的纬度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a fact that birds use to figure out their latitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.36,0:30:50.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球磁场中还存在着许多微小的不规则的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are also small irregularities in the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.03,0:30:52.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这些不规则的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}locations where the field
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.50,0:30:54.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}磁场会有强弱不同的变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a little weaker or stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.93,0:30:57.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像是独特的山脉和河流一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like a distinctive mountain or river,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.37,0:31:01.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些不一样的磁场也能作为地标\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these magnetic anomalies can serve as landmarks.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.18,0:31:14.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几千年来人们一直在使用信鸽\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For thousands of years, humans have used carrier pigeons
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.29,0:31:17.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在长距离传递信件\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to send messages to distant locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.19,0:31:19.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一种非常重要的信息传递方式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a crucial method of communication
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.36,0:31:21.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到了二战时也是如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as recently as World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.23,0:31:22.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 人类实际上也已经\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you think about it, we've been using
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.93,0:31:25.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}利用磁场来进行通讯有很长一段时间了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}magnetic fields to communicate for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.96,0:31:28.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是我们不知道而已\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We just didn't know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.97,0:31:39.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那地球为什么会有磁场呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So why does our planet have a magnetic field at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.64,0:31:41.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是如何产生的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What causes it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.41,0:31:44.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}答案就在地球的深处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The answer lies deep inside the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.65,0:31:49.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在地球自转的同时 液态的铁在绕着实心的地核旋转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Liquid iron, circulating around the solid part of the core as Earth rotates,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.32,0:31:53.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就好像是电流绕着线圈运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}acts like a wire carrying an electric current.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.09,0:31:54.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像法拉弟展示的那样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as Faraday showed us,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.93,0:31:57.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电流产生了磁场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}electric currents produce magnetic fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.50,0:31:59.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这对人类而言是件好事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.10,0:32:01.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}磁场让我们避免宇宙射线的猛烈攻击\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our magnetic field protects us from the onslaught
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:05.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}否则生物圈就会遭到巨大伤害\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of cosmic rays, which would be very damaging to our biosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.60,0:32:08.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙射线可以穿透\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cosmic rays can rip through DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.94,0:32:11.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有磁场的保护\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without our magnetic field, the rate of mutation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.34,0:32:13.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生物有机体的变异率会变高\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in living organisms would be much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.51,0:32:17.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}幸好 大部分的射线粒子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately, most of this cosmic shrapnel gets trapped
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.68,0:32:20.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会被范艾伦幅射带所困住 它看上去就像个甜甜圈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the Van Allen belts, donut-shaped zones
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.45,0:32:25.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带电的粒子会被地球磁场的防护层所拦下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of charged particles corralled by our magnetic shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:36.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}明白了地球自身就是一个大磁棒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Knowing that the Earth itself is like a giant bar magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.43,0:32:39.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们就可以解释天空中最美丽景观之一的形成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}explains one of the most beautiful sights in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.50,0:32:41.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是极光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the aurora.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.71,0:32:46.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来自太阳的带电粒子 也就是太阳风\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Charged particles from the Sun, the solar wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.31,0:32:49.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在不断地轰击地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are constantly bombarding the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.15,0:32:52.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以反把太阳风想象为某种电流\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can think of the solar wind as a kind of electric current.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.68,0:32:54.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的磁场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our planet's magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.79,0:32:57.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在把这股电流导向南极与北极 并在这之间形成了电流渠道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}channels that current towards the North and South Poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.46,0:32:59.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当它与大气碰撞时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it hits our atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.29,0:33:01.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空气中氧分子与氮分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the oxygen and nitrogen molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.13,0:33:05.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就会像巨大的荧光灯一样发出光芒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the air glow like giant fluorescent lightbulbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.08,0:33:28.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当法拉第在继续进行着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Faraday pursued
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.69,0:33:31.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最后也是最具有重大意义的发现时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}his last and most profound discovery,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.09,0:33:33.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}贫穷的童年对他的影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the poverty of his childhood stymied him
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.09,0:33:34.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比以往任何时刻都要明显的显现出来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it never had before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.86,0:33:36.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他需要帮助\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He needed help
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.59,0:33:39.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}结果 是另一个与他出身不同的人帮助了他\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and found it in one who had come from another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:33:56.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}法拉利解开了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Michael Faraday had solved the mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.91,0:33:59.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}困惑牛顿已久的谜团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that baffled Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.50,0:34:20.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是太阳如何令行星围绕着它运转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was how the Sun told the planets how to move
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.27,0:34:22.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又不用接触到它们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without touching them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.57,0:34:24.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳实际上还是接触得到行星的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun does touch the planets
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.77,0:34:26.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过它的引力场的作用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with its gravitational field,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.91,0:34:29.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而地球的引力场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Earth's gravitational field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.24,0:34:32.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}则告诉苹果何时该掉下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tells the apples how to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.55,0:34:44.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有这一切只是一个梦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All this is a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.16,0:34:48.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不幸的是 这就是当时的流行观点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately, that was the prevailing view
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.00,0:34:50.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与他同时代的科学家们认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}among his fellow scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.60,0:34:52.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}法拉弟在做梦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Faraday was dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.87,0:34:54.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们尊重他的创造能力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They admired his inventiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.50,0:34:56.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与他天才的实验能力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and his genius for experimentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.57,0:34:59.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他们认为他那看不见的「力线」\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they regarded his invisible "lines of force"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.41,0:35:02.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与他关于光和引力的观点是臆造的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and his ideas about light and gravity as hand-waving,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.88,0:35:06.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有任何可靠的实证可以支持\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}meaning there was nothing solid to back it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.21,0:35:09.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有人公开谴责他的理论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some openly ridiculed his theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.42,0:35:11.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们需要看到他的理论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They needed to see his ideas expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.75,0:35:14.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能被现代物理学的语言所解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the language of modern physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.22,0:35:15.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是精确的数学方程式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}precise equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.92,0:35:17.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而这个方面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was the one area
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.39,0:35:19.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由于法拉弟的童年很贫穷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where Faraday's childhood poverty
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.06,0:35:20.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有得到过正式的教育\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and lack of formal education
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.43,0:35:24.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此成为了他的缺陷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually held him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.03,0:35:26.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他不懂得数学运算\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He couldn't do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.73,0:35:31.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}法拉弟最终遇到了他无法跨越的障碍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Faraday had finally hit a wall that he could not overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.30,0:35:33.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而这时 另一位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, the greatest theoretical physicist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.91,0:35:36.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被公认为19世纪最伟大的理论物理学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the 19th century came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.74,0:35:40.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}詹姆斯・克拉克・麦克斯韦 出生在一个富裕的家庭里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}James Clerk Maxwell was born into a world of wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.91,0:35:42.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}家里很有权力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and privilege,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.55,0:35:46.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的父母中年得子 他是家里唯一的孩子 深得宠爱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an only child of doting middle-aged parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.56,0:35:54.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当他才20出头时 就已经\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By his early 20s, he had made a name for himself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.76,0:35:56.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成为一个知名的数学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a mathematician.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.50,0:35:58.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时其它的科学家认为法拉第\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While other scientists had come to think of Faraday
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.90,0:36:01.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经过时了 是历史遗老\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as old-fashioned; \N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a great figure of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.33,0:36:04.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根本就不是属于未来的物理学者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but no part of the future of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.17,0:36:07.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}麦克斯韦有不同的想法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}James Clerk Maxwell knew better.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.64,0:36:09.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他认真的阅读了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He began by reading everything
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.64,0:36:12.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}法拉弟所写的关于电学的一切著作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Faraday had written on electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.25,0:36:15.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他坚信法拉第所提到的力场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He became convinced that Faraday's fields of force
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.25,0:36:17.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是真实存在的 并且开始动手\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were real, and he set out to give them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.75,0:36:20.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用精确的数学方程式来证明这一切\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a precise mathematical formulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.39,0:36:54.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}论法拉第力线
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.80,0:37:09.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物理学中的数学方程式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An equation in physics is just a shorthand description
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.64,0:37:13.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是对某种在特定空间和时间中出现的物理现象的描述\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of something that can be represented in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.14,0:37:16.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}例如 描述钟摆弧线的方程式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For instance, the equation that describes the arc of a pendulum
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.58,0:37:21.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}描述了它无论如何也不可能摆动得比起始点高\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shows that it can never swing higher than its initial height.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.73,0:37:39.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当麦克斯韦把法拉利的实验现象转化为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Maxwell translated Faraday's experimental
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.90,0:37:43.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电磁学的方程式后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}observation on electromagnetic fields into equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:46.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他又发现了其中的不对称性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he discovered an asymmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.17,0:37:50.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看见底部那一条没有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that bottom one?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.18,0:37:52.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它急切地需要某些东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It cries out for something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.75,0:37:54.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}作为一位伟大的数学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Great mathematician that he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.75,0:37:58.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}麦克斯韦在其后加了一个单项以平衡方程式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maxwell added a single term to balance it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.22,0:38:01.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}方程式的这一调整改变了法拉弟的静态磁场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This tweaking of the equation changed Faraday's static field
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.89,0:38:05.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使它变成了能以光速向外传播的波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into waves that spread outward at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.76,0:38:09.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没过多久 人类就发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It wasn't long before we found a way to turn those waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.76,0:38:13.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把这些波转为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into couriers
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:15.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}传递信息工具的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for our messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.14,0:38:19.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能看到我吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.07,0:38:21.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能听到我吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.47,0:38:24.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是根源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is how.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.80,0:38:33.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这项技术改变了人类的文明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This technology has transformed human civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.37,0:38:35.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界从一个个东拼西凑起来的城市\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a patchwork of cities,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.50,0:38:37.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有小镇和乡村\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}towns and villages
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.51,0:38:41.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成了互通信息的社会组织体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into an intercommunicating organism...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.79,0:38:53.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}信息以光速进行传播\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}linking us at light speed...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.86,0:39:01.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}连接着地球上的每一个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.37,0:39:13.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至是宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.71,0:39:48.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世上的一切都很美好\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing is too wonderful to be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.98,0:39:52.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要它能符合自然规律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if it be consistent with the laws of nature.
